/* ============================================================
   DASHBOARD ECU — Board 2 — STM32F407 Discovery
   CAN Bus ECU Simulator — v4.0 FINAL

   WHAT THIS DOES:
   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   - Receives ALL CAN frames from Engine ECU (Board 1)
   - Displays on 1.8" ST7735 TFT (128×160):
       * RPM with large text
       * Speed (km/h)
       * Engine Temperature (°C)
       * System Mode: NORMAL / FAULT / LIMP / RECOVER
       * DTC code (when fault active)
   - Mirrors everything to UART (Putty)
   - Buzzer beeps on fault events received via CAN

   HARDWARE CONNECTIONS (Board 2):
   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   ST7735 TFT (1.8" 128×160):
     VCC  → 3.3V
     GND  → GND
     CS   → PA4  (SPI1 NSS  or GPIO)
     RESET→ PA3  (GPIO output)
     DC   → PA2  (GPIO output — Data/Command)
     SDA  → PA7  (SPI1 MOSI)
     SCK  → PA5  (SPI1 SCK)
     LED  → 3.3V (backlight always on) or PA1 (GPIO)

   CAN Bus:
     TX   → PD1 (CAN1 TX)
     RX   → PD0 (CAN1 RX)
     Use MCP2551 or SN65HVD230 transceiver
     Connect CAN H/L to Engine ECU Board 1

   Buzzer:
     +    → PE0 (GPIO output)
     –    → GND

   UART (Putty monitor):
     TX   → PA2 (USART2 TX — if not using for DC!)
     NOTE: If PA2 is used for TFT DC, use USART1 on PA9/PA10

   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   IMPORTANT: In CubeMX for Board 2:
   - Enable SPI1 (PA5=SCK, PA7=MOSI) — Transmit Only Master
   - SPI1 prescaler: divide by 4 = 42MHz/4 = 10.5MHz (ST7735 max 15MHz)
   - PA2=GPIO_Output (TFT DC)
   - PA3=GPIO_Output (TFT RESET)
   - PA4=GPIO_Output (TFT CS)
   - Enable CAN1 (PD0/PD1)
   - Enable USART1 PA9/PA10 at 115200 baud
   - Enable PE0 as GPIO_Output (buzzer)

   CAN FRAME PROTOCOL (received from Engine ECU):
   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   0x100 [2B] RPM         big-endian uint16
   0x101 [1B] Speed       km/h uint8
   0x102 [2B] Temp×10     big-endian uint16 (divide by 10 for °C)
   0x103 [1B] Relay       0x01=overtemp
   0x104 [1B] SysState    0=NORMAL,1=FAULT,2=LIMP,3=RECOVER
   0x1FF [3B] DTC         byte0,byte1,byte2
   ============================================================ */

